  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Extensive mesh-convergence studies, turbulence-model benchmarking against FDA nozzle data, and scalar transport verification against analytical solutions underpin the credibility argument. The numerical discretization error factor was evaluated across three systematically refined grids using Richardson extrapolation; the GCI-based uncertainty estimate of 4.2% on the predicted RH index is within the acceptance threshold of 5%, and the factor is considered satisfactorily addressed. Validation against the FDA benchmark centrifugal pump dataset at five operating points yields normalised RMS residuals below 3% for head rise and below 8% for hemolysis index, comfortably within the accepted tolerance bands for MRL 2. On this basis the assessment team judges the overall credibility evidence to be consistent with a Medium assurance level and recommends acceptance of the simulation results for the stated COU.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cpb-hemolysis-req-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cpb-hemolysis-claim-001",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/morrison-cpb-cfd-hemolysis-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-generic-cpb-benchmark-dataset",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/morrison-cpb-mesh-convergence-study",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/morrison-cpb-operating-point-sweeps"
  ],
  "hasContextOfUse": {
    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to evaluate the sensitivity of pump-induced hemolysis to variations in component dimensions for a centrifugal blood pump used during cardiopulmonary bypass surgery. Model influence is MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect tolerance decision could impact clinical hemolysis levels). Model Risk Level 2.",
    "deviceClass": "Class II",
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou1-cpb",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to identify worst-case operating conditions for hemolysis across 5 flow-speed combinations for a Class II CPB device. Results compared against predicate device hemolysis using relative hemolysis index (RH < 1 acceptance criterion).",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "name": "COU1: Cardiopulmonary bypass use (Class II)",
    "type": "ContextOfUse"
  },
